Pre-Phase-10 security audit + test infrastructure hardening

Comprehensive audit pass before Phase 10 (testnets + external
auditors). Four parallel investigative agents covered network /
crypto / VM-state / supply-chain attack surfaces; findings
synthesized into SECURITY_AUDIT.md with per-finding severity and
resolution status. This commit ships the actionable hardening
items + test infrastructure improvements; spec-author-required
items are documented as Phase 10 audit blockers.

# Test infrastructure shipped

## Property-based crypto round-trip coverage (proptest)

New crates/adamant-crypto/tests/proptest_roundtrips.rs with 15
property tests sweeping the input space for SHA3-256 domain
separation, ChaCha20-Poly1305 AEAD round-trip + tamper rejection
+ AAD binding, Ed25519 sign/verify + byte round-trips, BLS12-381
sign/verify + 3 byte round-trip variants, symmetric key byte
round-trip.

## Snapshot tests for consensus-binding wire types (insta)

New crates/adamant-consensus/tests/wire_snapshots.rs with 11
snapshot tests pinning the BCS byte layout of consensus-binding
types. Snapshots stored at tests/snapshots/; insta is workspace-
dev-only.

## Known-Answer Tests for derive_id + output_randomness

vertex.rs::derive_id_known_answer_vector pins the canonical
VertexId derivation under a fixed UnsignedVertex fixture.
vrf.rs::output_randomness_known_answer_vector pins the canonical
VRF randomness derivation. Both reviewable by hand.

## KZG + VDF cross-validation oracles

New crates/adamant-crypto/tests/kzg_vdf_oracles.rs with 12 KAT
tests covering derive_discriminant determinism + residue + width,
hash_to_element determinism, Wesolowski prove/verify round-trip +
tampered-h + wrong-T rejection + T=0/1/2 squaring pin, BQF
associativity + commutativity in real class groups (-23 and -20),
KZG public-surface pin.

## Strengthened error-variant test patterns

12 assert(matches(err, V { .. })) wildcards converted to
destructure-and-compare across commit_sequencer.rs (2), dag.rs
(2), light_client.rs (2), slashing.rs (3), phase_7_pipeline.rs
(1), anti_dos.rs (2). Each strengthened assertion checks specific
field values, catching the bug class where the right variant
fires with wrong contents.

## Hardened select_index against 32-bit truncation

Comment previously claimed "truncates the high bits on 32-bit"
which was mathematically wrong. The cast is structurally lossless
on both platforms because r % n_u64 < n <= usize::MAX. Fixed
comment + added two regression tests pinning bit-exact output
under known inputs + platform-independence at small n.

## Domain-tag uniqueness invariant tests

New uniqueness_tests module in adamant-crypto::domain enumerates
all 32 production domain tags + asserts byte-distinctness +
shared ADAMANT-v1- prefix. Defense-in-depth for the §3.3.1
tagged-hash discipline.

# Resistant-proof guard expanded

crates/adamant-vm/tests/no_sui_in_production_deps.rs now also
guards the broader Sui-ecosystem surface (sui-, narwhal-, mysten-
prefixes) per CLAUDE.md §13 + §14. Original move- guard catches
the bytecode-verifier case; new guard extends to the broader
family. Both tests pass.

# Security audit findings

Four parallel investigative agents (network / crypto / VM-state /
supply-chain) audited the protocol. Full findings in
SECURITY_AUDIT.md. Headlines:

## Actionable hardening shipped here

- Crypto L-1: Domain-tag uniqueness regression tests. FIXED.
- Network H-3: RateLimiter unbounded growth - added
  max_tracked_peers cap (default 100k) + rejection path +
  regression test. FIXED.

## Phase 10 audit blockers (SPEC-AUTHOR-REQUIRED, top priority)

1. Crypto C-1: RecursiveProofPublicInputs are NOT bound into
   the proof. Light client accepts forged commitments under
   valid-but-unrelated accumulators. Breaks §8.5.1 soundness.
2. Crypto C-2: BLS aggregate verify accepts rogue-key attack -
   no proof-of-possession at validator registration. Breaks
   §8.6 VRF + every BLS-aggregate consensus check.
3. Privacy H-4: BindingSignature has no verify surface. §7.3.2
   statement 4 (homomorphic balance) is unenforceable on-chain.

Each requires spec-author amendment. Documented in
SECURITY_AUDIT.md.

## Other DEFERRED-TO-PHASE-10 items

Network H-1/2/4/5/6, VM C-1/2/3, Supply-chain H-1/2/3. Full list
+ resolution venues in SECURITY_AUDIT.md.

## Audit-confirmed clean categories

Concurrency posture, unsafe isolation (51 blocks all in
adamant-crypto-blst-extra with SAFETY comments), gas accounting,
sparse Merkle tree soundness, bytecode deserializer canonicality,
Rule 5 deprecated-global-storage enforcement, constant-time
discipline, zero build.rs, all sources crates.io only.

